## Architectural Preservation Rules

Define how milestone planning must preserve epic architecture.

| ID | Architectural Rule | Applies To | Required Behavior |
|---|---|---|---|

Examples:

- do not invent new architecture
- preserve abstraction boundaries
- preserve capability ownership
- preserve compatibility boundaries
- preserve dependency direction
- mark underspecified architecture as follow-up
- do not resolve architectural ambiguity by redesigning the epic

## Dependency Inheritance Rules

Define how milestone dependencies should be represented.

| ID | Dependency Rule | Applies When | Required Behavior |
|---|---|---|---|

Examples:

- upstream milestones must be explicit
- downstream milestones enabled must be explicit
- prerequisite completion evidence must be explicit
- inherited assumptions must be represented
- inherited constraints must be represented
- dependency uncertainty must become follow-up
- dependent milestone cannot be treated as executable before prerequisite completion

