- scope is clear
- dependencies are explicit
- constraints are explicit
- assumptions are marked
- acceptance criteria are auditable
- validation strategy is clear
- deferred work is explicit
- follow-up items are resolved or marked
- architecture ambiguity is not hidden

Failure Handling should explain whether to mark required follow-up, block execution prompt generation, or return to epic correction.

## Blocking Rules

Define when GenerateMilestoneDeepDivesForEpic should refuse or partially block generation.

| ID | Blocking Case | Indicates | Required Handling |
|---|---|---|---|

